==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sephardic
<hw>Se*phar"dic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Sephardim</ets>, a name applied to the Spanish Jews, fr.
<etsep>Sephard</etsep>, name of a place where Jews were held in
captivity (<au>Ob. 20</au>).]</ety> <def>Of, pertaining to, or
designating, the Jews (the <xex>Sephardim</xex>, also called
<xex>Spanish</xex> or <xex>Portuguese Jews</xex>) descended from Jewish
families driven from Spain by the Inquisition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sephardim</ent>⟦br⟧
